Modelaci√≥n Reto

Multiple mass-spring-damper model
  • The walls are assumed to be flexible and massless.
  • The floors are assumed to be rigid masses connected by spring-dampers (the walls).
  • Only horizontal motion is modeled.
  • The parameters have been rescaled to and are treated as unitless. These parameters were not selected to reflect the mass or stiffness of a real structure. Instead, they were selected to produce realistic oscillation frequencies.
Mass-spring-damper building model
